docs.abstract: The police commissioner sent a valuable message by firing the New York City officer who put Mr. Garner in a chokehold that turned fatal.
docs.snippet: The police commissioner sent a valuable message by firing the New York City officer who put Mr. Garner in a chokehold that turned fatal.
docs.lead_paragraph: As he announced that he was firing the police officer who had put Eric Garner in the chokehold that led to his death, New York City’s police commissioner, James O’Neill, sent the country’s largest police force a message: You may not think I’m on your side, but I am.
